@startuml
title 3D Human Pose Tracking System - Control Flow Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Webcam Client 1" as WC1
participant "Webcam Client 2" as WC2
participant "Node.js Server\n(Express + Socket.IO)" as Server
participant "Receiver Client" as Receiver
participant "GraphXR\nVisualization" as GraphXR

== System Initialization ==
User -> Server: Start HTTPS Server
activate Server
Server -> Server: Initialize Express.js
Server -> Server: Configure CORS middleware
Server -> Server: Initialize Socket.IO
Server --> User: Server ready on port
deactivate Server

== Client Connection ==
WC1 -> Server: Connect via Socket.IO
activate Server
Server -> WC1: Connection established
deactivate Server

WC2 -> Server: Connect via Socket.IO
activate Server
Server -> WC2: Connection established
deactivate Server

Receiver -> Server: Connect via Socket.IO
activate Server
Server -> Receiver: Connection established
deactivate Server

== Real-time Pose Tracking ==
loop Continuous Pose Estimation
    WC1 -> WC1: Capture video frame
    activate WC1
    WC1 -> WC1: Run PoseNet/MoveNet
    WC1 -> WC1: Extract 2D pose keypoints
    WC1 -> Server: Emit 'skeleton' event\n(2D pose data)
    deactivate WC1

    activate Server
    Server -> Server: Receive skeleton data
    Server -> Server: Process pose data
    Server -> Receiver: Broadcast skeleton data
    Server -> GraphXR: Broadcast skeleton data
    deactivate Server

    WC2 -> WC2: Capture video frame
    activate WC2
    WC2 -> WC2: Run PoseNet/MoveNet
    WC2 -> WC2: Extract 2D pose keypoints
    WC2 -> Server: Emit 'skeleton' event\n(2D pose data)
    deactivate WC2

    activate Server
    Server -> Server: Receive skeleton data
    Server -> Server: Combine 2D poses\nfrom orthogonal cameras
    Server -> Server: Reconstruct 3D pose
    Server -> Receiver: Broadcast 3D skeleton data
    Server -> GraphXR: Broadcast 3D skeleton data
    deactivate Server

    activate Receiver
    Receiver -> Receiver: Process 3D pose data
    Receiver -> Receiver: Update application state
    deactivate Receiver

    activate GraphXR
    GraphXR -> GraphXR: Render 3D skeleton
    GraphXR -> GraphXR: Update visualization
    deactivate GraphXR
end

== Data Visualization ==
User -> GraphXR: View 3D skeleton
activate GraphXR
GraphXR -> GraphXR: Load configuration\n(skel.grove, skelly.graphxr)
GraphXR -> GraphXR: Render real-time skeleton
GraphXR --> User: Display 3D pose visualization
deactivate GraphXR

== Client Disconnection ==
WC1 -> Server: Disconnect
activate Server
Server -> Server: Handle disconnection
Server --> WC1: Connection closed
deactivate Server

WC2 -> Server: Disconnect
activate Server
Server -> Server: Handle disconnection
Server --> WC2: Connection closed
deactivate Server

Receiver -> Server: Disconnect
activate Server
Server -> Server: Handle disconnection
Server --> Receiver: Connection closed
deactivate Server

@enduml
